                            <Label Text="AUDIENCE REVIEWS &#10;" FontSize="22" FontAttributes="Bold" TextColor="Black"/>

                            <StackLayout Orientation="Horizontal" Spacing="10">
                                <Image Source="https://i.ibb.co/HTKDnKz/person-icon.png" HeightRequest="40"/>
                                <Label Text="Amy Nicholson &#10;2 months ago " FontAttributes="Bold" TextColor="Black" FontSize="13" CharacterSpacing="0.5"/>
                                <Image Source="https://i.ibb.co/Bs7bnky/5.png" WidthRequest="70"/>
                            </StackLayout>
                            <Label Text="There's nothing as good as Back to the Future, but I think Levy finds the heart to this picture. It really works.&#10;" TextColor="#37383b" FontSize="15" CharacterSpacing="0.2" />

                            <StackLayout Orientation="Horizontal" Spacing="10">
                                <Image Source="https://i.ibb.co/HTKDnKz/person-icon.png" HeightRequest="40"/>
                                <Label Text="Sean P. Means &#10;3 months ago" FontAttributes="Bold" TextColor="Black" FontSize="13" CharacterSpacing="0.5"/>
                                <Image Source="https://i.ibb.co/5v61tGY/3-stars.png" WidthRequest="70"/>
                            </StackLayout>
                            <Label Text="When Levy tries to get serious and introspective, as little Adam forces Big Adam to confront the psychological pain of losing his father, the movie discovers a new kind of cinematic time travel by making the film slow to a crawl.&#10;" TextColor="#37383b" FontSize="15" CharacterSpacing="0.2" />

                            <StackLayout Orientation="Horizontal" Spacing="10">
                                <Image Source="https://i.ibb.co/HTKDnKz/person-icon.png" HeightRequest="40"/>
                                <Label Text="rallder19 &#10;3 months ago " FontAttributes="Bold" TextColor="Black" FontSize="13" CharacterSpacing="0.5"/>
                                <Image Source="https://i.ibb.co/7XwtYVb/4.png" WidthRequest="70"/>
                            </StackLayout>
                            <Label Text="This isn't going to win any Oscars, and it is far from a perfect time travel movie, but it was a fun ride. Kept my interest all the way through and had a good cast.&#10;" TextColor="#37383b" FontSize="15" CharacterSpacing="0.2" />

                            <StackLayout Orientation="Horizontal" Spacing="10">
                                <Image Source="https://i.ibb.co/HTKDnKz/person-icon.png" HeightRequest="40"/>
                                <Label Text="joiningjt &#10;3 months ago" FontAttributes="Bold" TextColor="Black" FontSize="13" CharacterSpacing="0.5"/>
                                <Image Source="https://i.ibb.co/Bs7bnky/5.png" WidthRequest="70"/>
                            </StackLayout>
                            <Label Text="Excellent cast excellent script, excellent special effects, and for a streaming action comedy PHENOMENAL final product. I found it far superior to red notice and that film was extremely expensive this also had a lot of heart. We especially loved the ending it tugs at your heart a few times during the film and especially at the end and when a film can be entertaining and make you think you have a winner!!&#10;" TextColor="#37383b" FontSize="15" CharacterSpacing="0.2" />

                            <StackLayout Orientation="Horizontal" Spacing="10">
                                <Image Source="https://i.ibb.co/HTKDnKz/person-icon.png" HeightRequest="40"/>
                                <Label Text="Sarah Knight Adamson &#10;2 months ago" FontAttributes="Bold" TextColor="Black" FontSize="13" CharacterSpacing="0.5"/>
                                <Image Source="https://i.ibb.co/7XwtYVb/4.png" WidthRequest="70"/>
                            </StackLayout>
                            <Label Text="The delightful scenes between both older and younger Adam are the films crux, providing a pleasant viewing experience for families--Reynolds is a natural when comedy is involved, and viewing him yet again in a sci-fi role is a treat.&#10;" TextColor="#37383b" FontSize="15" CharacterSpacing="0.2" />

                            <StackLayout Orientation="Horizontal" Spacing="10">
                                <Image Source="https://i.ibb.co/HTKDnKz/person-icon.png" HeightRequest="40"/>
                                <Label Text="Daniel M. Kimmel &#10;3 months ago " FontAttributes="Bold" TextColor="Black" FontSize="13" CharacterSpacing="0.5"/>
                                <Image Source="https://i.ibb.co/5v61tGY/3-stars.png" WidthRequest="70"/>
                            </StackLayout>
                            <Label Text="The solid cast invests the story with emotion and some humor, Reynolds occasional snarkiness provides a nice counterpoint to Scobells mix of tween angst and excitement about the future.&#10;" TextColor="#37383b" FontSize="15" CharacterSpacing="0.2" />

